In [74]:



     


f0 = 220 # Hz
freqs = freqs = f0 * 2**(np.arange(n_examples) / 12)

for freq, example, a in zip(freqs, examples, activations):
    start_id = len(example) - 400
    end_id = len(example)
    
    sample_ids = np.arange(len(example))[start_id:end_id]
    ts = sample_ids / SR
    duration_samples = round(duration_ms * 1e-3 * SR)
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, dpi=150, sharex=True)
    fig.suptitle('%.2f Hz' % freq)
    
    axes[0].set_title('Generated example')
    axes[0].plot(ts, example[start_id:end_id])
    t0 = (len(example) - duration_samples) / SR
    axes[0].axvline(t0, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1)
    
    channels = (0, 0, 0)
    padded_a = np.full(len(example), np.nan)
    padded_a[-duration_samples:] = a[:, channels[0], channels[1], channels[2]]
    axes[1].set_title(f'Layer 15, channel {channels} activation')
    axes[1].plot(ts, padded_a[start_id:end_id])
    
    axes[-1].set_xlabel('Time (secs)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
    display(HTML('Generated example'))
    display(Audio(example.numpy(), rate=SR))
